What is Kubernetes ?

It is an Orchestration tool where we can manage and deploy the containerized applications through pods and expose them via service


Components:-

API Server
Scheduler
Controller Manager
Kubelet
Kube-proxy
ETCD


Features:-

Deployment: It helps to maintain the desired no. of pods are running and rollout, update and scale the pods
Service: It helps to expose the pods to outside world


Types:-
Cluster-IP
NodePort
LoadBalancer


External Name service: It helps to map the custom name to third party application such as AWS RDS-Endpoint
Ingress: It helps to provide the internal HTTP/HTTPS routing to the application
Headless Service: It helps to provide the DNS resolution to pods
StatefulSet: It used for databases and persists the data
DaemonSet: It ensures that one pod is running on each node
Cluster-Autoscaler: It helps to automatically scale the nodes based on cluster capacity
Horizontal-Pod-Autoscaler : It helps to automatically scale the pods based on pod metrics
Vertical-Pod-Autoscaler:  It helps to automatically adjust the CPU & Memory limits of the pods
RBAC:  It helps to provide the rule and permissions via roles, role-bindings and service-accounts
Secrets: It helps to store the sensitive data like credentials, passwords, username etc
ConfigMaps: It helps to store the Non-sensitive data like Database name, Hostname and port etc
Kubeconfig-file: It contains the cluster information

















